cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "The Agentic Trust Protocol: Path-Level Safety Architecture for LLM Agents"
message: "If you use this software or its scenarios, please cite this work."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Wagle"
    given-names: "Mihir"
abstract: >
  A research prototype demonstrating path-level safety architecture for
  LLM agents. Implements a CQRS-style separation of read and write
  paths inside a Plan-then-Execute structure, with a trust budget
  approximating the path integral of irreversibility, a staging area
  exposing proposed trajectories before execution, and a per-action
  irreversibility classifier. Includes evaluation scenarios organized
  by composition mode (quantity, premise, classification, iteration)
  for empirical study of when path-level architecture is necessary
  beyond per-call alignment.
keywords:
  - "AI safety"
  - "LLM agents"
  - "path-level safety"
  - "trust budget"
  - "irreversibility"
  - "agent architecture"
  - "Plan-then-Execute"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/mavaali/agentic-trust-protocol"
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-04-25"
